<br>
To me, it makes sense from a RP (not that it matters) to give wizards (the masters of spell based DD) the ability to imbue some of that power to equipment.  Whether this appears as a proc or a damage adjustment similiar to bane or magic damage really doesnt matter all that much, but this is definetly something that would give us an interesting and unique dimension. The only danger here is that the increased damage has to be enough to make the buff interesting to others and cheap enough in mana cost to make casting the buff worthwhile over just using the same mana to kick out a couple of extra nukes while at the same time not making the buff so powerful as to drastically change the difficulty of encounters in both exp groups and raids.<br>
<br>
Vaeldayanie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iumdidar>iumdidar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 12:24:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> overpowering</span><hr size=1> yes a bit overpowered <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
